observationText: The T3M-10 cell line produced three forms of colony stimulating factor (CSF) with estimated molecular weights of 47,000, 33,000 and 25,000 based on gel filtration chromatography, with the highest molecular weight form potentially related to normal lung CSF.

The T3M-10 cell line was established from an undifferentiated large cell lung carcinoma and continuously propagated for at least 28 months, exhibiting epithelial-like morphology and a population doubling time of 46 hours.
The T3M-10 cell line had an aneuploid karyotype with a near-diploid modal chromosome number of 47 and no normal metaphases observed.
